ir production, circulation, and consumption. To illuminate this bold argument, Edney chronicles precisely how the ideal of cartography that has developed in the West since 1800 has gone astray. By exposing the flaws in this ideal, his book challenges everyone who studies maps and mapping practices to reexamine their approach to the topic. The study of cartography will never be the same.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCartographyxPhilosophyxHistory. 0aCartographyxPhilosophy. 7aTechnology & Engineering / General.2bisacsh  acartography.  ageometry.  ahistory of cartography.  amap history.  amap scale.  amapping processes.  amapping.  atheory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311071194340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226605715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226605715.jpg  a978-3-11-071194-3  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles